  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6590.57 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6500 (-4.5B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+8.3B), dealers are in active hedging mode and likely selling delta into any push toward 6605 while preparing to buy aggressively on dips toward 6500. The PIN regime confirms dealers are long gamma and will provide stabilizing flows, but the recent regime flip and GEX surge (147% in 1-min) suggests we just saw significant options positioning changes that could create temporary volatility before mean reversion kicks in. Key levels are crystal clear: 6605 represents massive dealer selling pressure while 6500 is where dealers will step in with heavy buying support.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 6500-6605 with dealers capping upside and defending downside.",
